Here’s the clean, updated, repo-ready version with migi replacing tigi and semantics tightened.

⸻

beast-language-acronyms-special-definitions.md

purpose

define short-form beast language signals used for fast, low-latency communication

these are not casual slang

they are semantic control signals

each term encodes:
	•	confidence level
	•	system state
	•	recommended next action

goal:
	•	reduce verbosity
	•	increase alignment speed
	•	minimize illusion of understanding

⸻

core signal set

lgtm

lgtm = i believe it is good enough to proceed

meaning:
	•	positive evaluation
	•	sufficient confidence to act

implication:
	•	proceed
	•	monitor for issues

notes:
	•	not certainty
	•	decision threshold, not truth threshold

⸻

wtf

wtf = i believe something is wrong

meaning:
	•	system conflict
	•	unexpected or inconsistent result

implication:
	•	stop
	•	inspect
	•	debug

notes:
	•	diagnostic signal
	•	not emotional outburst

⸻

idk

idk = i do not know

meaning:
	•	no reliable internal model
	•	explicit uncertainty

implication:
	•	ask
	•	search
	•	defer
	•	do not guess blindly

notes:
	•	preserves system integrity
	•	preferred over false confidence

⸻

migi

migi = maybe i got it

meaning:
	•	partial understanding
	•	~50/50 confidence
	•	working model exists but unverified

implication:
	•	proceed cautiously
	•	confirm key ambiguity if needed

notes:
	•	midpoint between idk and lgtm
	•	avoids false certainty
	•	preferred over "tigi" due to clearer uncertainty signal

⸻

additional signals

glitch

glitch = unexpected but possibly minor anomaly

meaning:
	•	deviation from expected behavior
	•	not yet confirmed as failure

implication:
	•	observe
	•	reproduce
	•	escalate if persistent

notes:
	•	softer than wtf
	•	does not imply full system break

⸻

epic

epic = significantly above standard, stands out

meaning:
	•	high quality
	•	notable improvement over baseline

implication:
	•	highlight
	•	preserve
	•	consider reuse or sharing

notes:
	•	evaluation signal, not control signal

⸻

sptm

sptm = subjectively perfect to me

meaning:
	•	deeply reviewed
	•	fully aligned with personal standards

implication:
	•	preserve
	•	potentially elevate to "diamond" artifact

notes:
	•	explicitly subjective
	•	used after careful evaluation
	•	may be written out in full when emphasis matters

⸻

semantic ladder

idk    → no model
migi   → partial (~50/50)
lgtm   → actionable confidence
epic   → stands out
sptm   → personally perfect
wtf    → model conflict / failure
glitch → anomaly detected


⸻

usage patterns

confirmation loop

